title: Why 'big moment' of Israel invasion may not happen
description: In the hours and days after the 7 October attacks on Israel, the sense coming from the Israeli military and government was of an imminent ground invasion to avenge the massacre of their people.

title: Pro-Russia politician shot in Crimea attack
description: A pro-Russia politician has been shot and wounded in a late-night attack in Crimea, family and officials have said.

title: Former crypto boss admits 'mistakes' but denies $10bn theft
description: Former crypto tycoon Sam Bankman-Fried has admitted he made "mistakes" in how he ran his collapsed FTX exchange - but told a court he did not steal from its customers.

title: 'We are paying a very high price': Anger in West Bank as Israel offensive intensifies
description: A soldier with his machine gun cradled in his arms signals us to stop as we approach a checkpoint on the road to the West Bank city of Nablus.

title: IDF says it is 'acting with great force' as ground operations in Gaza expanded
description: Israel will expand ground operations tonight and has warned residents of Gaza City to move south.

title: Ivanka Trump must give evidence against her father in fraud case, judge rules
description: A judge has decided Ivanka Trump must testify in the civil fraud case against her father, brothers, and their family business.

title: 'Gaza is being strangled': UN urges Israel to allow more aid amid 'collective punishment' blockade
description: Israel must allow more aid into Gaza amid a blockade that is being used to "collectively punish more than two million people", a UN official has said.

title: Israel accuses Hamas of launching attacks from inside Gaza hospitals - and signals it could target medical facilities
description: Israel accused Hamas of launching attacks from hospitals in Gaza, said this was a war crime and signalled that such action could make medical facilities a legitimate target.

title: Ex-navy men sentenced to death on mysterious espionage charges
description: Eight former Indian navy men have been sentenced to death in Qatar on espionage charges.

title: Israel carries out second ground raid in Gaza amid 'humanitarian catastrophe' warning
description: Israeli forces backed by warplanes and drones have carried out a second ground raid in Gaza as aid trickles into the besieged territory amid warnings of a deepening "humanitarian catastrophe".

title: Search called off for crew members missing after British cargo ship sank off German coast
description: A search for four people missing after two ships crashed off the coast of Germany has been called off.

title: Italian mum wins court order to evict her 40 and 42-year-old sons
description: An Italian mum has won a court battle to evict her two sons - aged 40 and 42 - from her home in the northern city of Pavia, according to local media.

title: Before and after images as deadly hurricane leaves multibillion-pound path of destruction in Mexico
description: A swathe of destruction left after one of the most powerful storms ever to hit Mexico battered the beach resort of Acapulco, killing at least 27 people, has been laid bare by aerial images.

title: Putin sets date for launch of Russia's new space station
description: Russia's new space station will come online in 2027, Vladimir Putin has said.

title: US and China relations have stabilised but much still divides them
description: There is likely to be a relative amount of cautious optimism from both the US and Chinese camps regarding the efforts to try and stabilise their relations.

title: China's former deputy leader dies from heart attack
description: China's former deputy leader Li Keqiang has died after suffering a heart attack.

title: US launches retaliatory strikes on Iran-linked munition storage sites in Syria
description: The US military has launched retaliatory airstrikes on two locations in eastern Syria linked to Iran's Revolutionary Guard Corps, the Pentagon has said.
